WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.047 --> 00:00:08.466
♪ You don't owe me ♪

2
00:00:08.550 --> 00:00:11.761
♪ One more minute of your wasted time ♪

3
00:00:12.887 --> 00:00:15.724
♪ You act like it's all fine ♪

4
00:00:16.307 --> 00:00:17.726
♪ It isn't hard to leave ♪

5
00:00:17.809 --> 00:00:21.354
♪ Knowing that I'll be getting life
On track ♪

6
00:00:22.689 --> 00:00:25.817
♪ I wanted to believe ♪

7
00:00:25.900 --> 00:00:32.657
♪ I've gotta make a destination ♪

8
00:00:32.741 --> 00:00:35.618
♪ Find where I belong ♪

9
00:00:35.702 --> 00:00:42.584
♪ This time I've got no hesitation ♪

10
00:00:42.667 --> 00:00:45.670
♪ I'll be movin' on ♪

11
00:00:45.754 --> 00:00:49.132
♪ To where I belong ♪

12
00:00:49.215 --> 00:00:52.260
♪ I'll be movin' on ♪

13
00:00:52.343 --> 00:00:55.722
♪ Over the line I've drawn ♪

14
00:00:55.805 --> 00:01:01.061
♪ I'm already gone ♪

15
00:01:03.000 --> 00:01:09.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

16
00:01:14.699 --> 00:01:16.993
He tried to run in.
Couldn't get him to stop.

17
00:01:17.077 --> 00:01:18.078
Yeah.

18
00:01:19.120 --> 00:01:22.207
♪ You live to fight my friend
You must expire ♪

19
00:01:23.917 --> 00:01:27.378
♪ Take your clothes
And throw them in the fire ♪

20
00:01:28.630 --> 00:01:31.466
♪ We were born into a world of flames ♪

21
00:01:33.384 --> 00:01:37.514
♪ Takes you back
And pushes you back again ♪

22
00:01:38.306 --> 00:01:40.141
The investigation will take a few days.

23
00:01:40.225 --> 00:01:43.561
but the preliminary assessment indicates
the fire started in the garage.

24
00:01:43.645 --> 00:01:45.271
probably due to the usual suspects.

25
00:01:45.355 --> 00:01:48.525
Faulty wiring. greasy rags.
items of that nature.

26
00:01:48.608 --> 00:01:51.444
You should reach out
to your insurance company now.

27
00:02:01.830 --> 00:02:04.874
There is nothing left to do tonight.
Come home with us.

28
00:02:06.501 --> 00:02:09.879
No. Iris is here. You have a houseful.
It's too much of an imposition.

29
00:02:09.963 --> 00:02:12.423
We have room. We will make room.

30
00:02:12.507 --> 00:02:14.634
Annie could stay with us.

31
00:02:14.717 --> 00:02:17.470
That is. if Uncle Erik
and Miss Helen don't mind.

32
00:02:17.554 --> 00:02:20.390
That would be better
for Aunt Maddie. right?

33
00:02:20.974 --> 00:02:22.976
Jessica's right. We have the room.

34
00:02:23.059 --> 00:02:24.644
Please. Dana Sue. let us help.

35
00:02:24.727 --> 00:02:26.980
Ugh… I mean. uh…

36
00:02:27.063 --> 00:02:27.939
Blake?

37
00:02:28.523 --> 00:02:31.276
Please. will you take
Annie and Jessica to my house?

38
00:02:31.359 --> 00:02:33.278
-Sure.
-I appreciate that. Helen.

39
00:02:33.361 --> 00:02:35.321
-Watch the speed limit. Blake.
-Yes. sir.

40
00:02:39.033 --> 00:02:41.494
Let me pack up a few more things.

41
00:02:41.578 --> 00:02:44.038
♪ Take me as I am ♪

42
00:02:45.748 --> 00:02:46.875
See you there.

43
00:02:46.958 --> 00:02:48.710
♪ Take me as I am ♪

44
00:02:50.753 --> 00:02:52.964
♪ The water's coming fast ♪

45
00:02:54.215 --> 00:02:57.844
-Hey. Let's go.
-♪ Take me as I am ♪

46
00:02:58.553 --> 00:03:00.180
Come on.

47
00:03:00.263 --> 00:03:02.724
♪ The water's coming fast ♪

48
00:03:10.356 --> 00:03:11.733
To soothe your nerves.

49
00:03:17.739 --> 00:03:18.865
Annie's safe.

50
00:03:19.407 --> 00:03:20.700
So are you.

51
00:03:22.452 --> 00:03:25.330
Fresh linens on the bed.
fresh towels in the bathroom.

52
00:03:25.413 --> 00:03:30.043
and there are extra pillows to be had.
depending on your elevation preference.

53
00:03:30.627 --> 00:03:32.086
You've both had a night.

54
00:03:32.170 --> 00:03:33.296
It's late.

55
00:03:34.005 --> 00:03:35.465
Some rest might be good.

56
00:03:50.438 --> 00:03:52.982
We. uh… we thought you'd be asleep by now.

57
00:03:53.983 --> 00:03:54.859
Where's Annie?

58
00:03:54.943 --> 00:03:57.278
I've set Annie up in the trundle
in my guest bedroom

59
00:03:57.362 --> 00:03:59.322
with everything
that she needs for tonight.

60
00:03:59.405 --> 00:04:02.408
Towels. a sleep shirt. and now ice cream.

61
00:04:02.492 --> 00:04:03.660
Mm.

62
00:04:04.827 --> 00:04:06.329
Would you guys like some?

63
00:04:06.412 --> 00:04:07.664
Annie's gonna need a toothbrush.

64
00:04:07.747 --> 00:04:09.916
especially after eating
all that ice cream.

65
00:04:10.708 --> 00:04:11.876
I have extras.

66
00:04:17.048 --> 00:04:19.050
I found some cones in the cupboard.

67
00:04:19.133 --> 00:04:20.677
Uh. no. thanks.

68
00:04:21.177 --> 00:04:22.053
Excuse me.

69
00:04:32.146 --> 00:04:34.482
What are you doing down here?

70
00:04:34.565 --> 00:04:36.943
You said you were gonna come to bed
after your shower.

71
00:04:37.443 --> 00:04:40.280
I… haven't.

72
00:04:51.833 --> 00:04:53.960
How do we get through this. Ronnie?

73
00:04:54.502 --> 00:04:55.712
I wish I knew.

74
00:05:02.010 --> 00:05:03.011
I'm sorry.

75
00:05:03.094 --> 00:05:04.595
This is my fault.

76
00:05:05.096 --> 00:05:06.180
The fire?

77
00:05:08.516 --> 00:05:09.392
Ronnie.

78
00:05:10.518 --> 00:05:15.064
I… I should have been taking care
of whatever caused it.

79
00:05:16.774 --> 00:05:19.235
I've been focused on the wrong things.

80
00:05:21.779 --> 00:05:22.697
And I'm…

81
00:05:24.699 --> 00:05:25.700
I'm sorry.

82
00:05:32.790 --> 00:05:33.750
Yeah.

83
00:05:36.002 --> 00:05:36.961
Me too.

84
00:05:43.843 --> 00:05:45.803
Sorry. I'm not interested.

85
00:05:46.387 --> 00:05:47.347
Not interested?

86
00:05:47.847 --> 00:05:49.974
-I feared this day would come.
-You're here.

87
00:05:50.058 --> 00:05:50.892
I am.

88
00:05:50.975 --> 00:05:53.311
But I texted last night.
and we agreed to reschedule

89
00:05:53.394 --> 00:05:55.188
because of what happened to Dana Sue.

90
00:05:55.688 --> 00:05:59.275
Exactly. I was supposed
to arrive tomorrow afternoon.

91
00:05:59.359 --> 00:06:00.318
Yeah. so…

92
00:06:00.401 --> 00:06:01.986
You told me about the fire.

93
00:06:02.612 --> 00:06:06.115
and I knew I had to be here for you
while you were taking care of your people.

94
00:06:06.199 --> 00:06:09.285
You rescheduled and came early.

95
00:06:09.369 --> 00:06:11.245
Politely early.

96
00:06:11.329 --> 00:06:15.208
I could have been here at 3:00 a.m..
but I knew you needed your sleep.

97
00:06:15.708 --> 00:06:18.002
And if I arrived at 3:00…

98
00:06:18.086 --> 00:06:21.297
Well. no one would have gotten any sleep.

99
00:06:44.821 --> 00:06:46.447
Okay. you about done?

100
00:06:48.574 --> 00:06:51.119
Chief Holbrook said
he can only give us two hours here.

101
00:06:51.202 --> 00:06:53.454
Why… why are you unpacking. not packing?

102
00:06:53.538 --> 00:06:54.872
Stop.

103
00:06:54.956 --> 00:06:58.251
You're not distinguishing between
what can be saved and what can't be.

104
00:06:58.334 --> 00:07:01.295
You're just throwing things
into boxes all pell-mell.

105
00:07:01.379 --> 00:07:03.798
We don't have time to be sentimental.

106
00:07:03.881 --> 00:07:06.551
I'm not sentimental. I'm grieving.

107
00:07:06.634 --> 00:07:09.053
By hanging on to things
that are singed and charred?

108
00:07:09.137 --> 00:07:10.638
By holding on to what I value.

109
00:07:11.305 --> 00:07:12.223
That old thing?

110
00:07:12.306 --> 00:07:14.976
This old thing was my mother's.

111
00:07:15.059 --> 00:07:16.978
and like Augusto saw.
I cook from my heart.

112
00:07:17.061 --> 00:07:18.896
I got that from her.

113
00:07:20.189 --> 00:07:23.818
-That's what you use for your Bolognese.
-My mother's Bolognese.

114
00:07:23.901 --> 00:07:25.403
And her pot survived.

115
00:07:26.696 --> 00:07:28.406
Fine. keep it.

116
00:07:28.489 --> 00:07:31.284
but we have to pack up everything
and get out.

117
00:07:31.367 --> 00:07:32.952
There could be more survivors.

118
00:07:39.625 --> 00:07:42.462
Courtney needs you. Of course.

119
00:07:42.545 --> 00:07:46.090
Nope. that was Jeremy checking on us.

120
00:07:49.135 --> 00:07:51.888
We cannot pick through the ashes.

121
00:07:52.889 --> 00:07:57.018
All we have are ashes. Ronnie.
and if we don't pick through them.

122
00:07:57.101 --> 00:08:00.438
important and valuable things
are gonna get thrown away.

123
00:08:01.564 --> 00:08:02.607
And we will regret it.

124
00:08:22.543 --> 00:08:24.170
Blake. hi.

125
00:08:24.754 --> 00:08:25.963
Nice to see you.

126
00:08:26.047 --> 00:08:27.131
Annie here?

127
00:08:27.840 --> 00:08:28.758
Come on in.

128
00:08:29.717 --> 00:08:30.885
Down that way.

129
00:08:35.181 --> 00:08:38.434
I hung everything out in the fresh air.
and I still smell smoke.

130
00:08:38.518 --> 00:08:39.602
Blake.

131
00:08:40.102 --> 00:08:41.479
I wasn't expecting you.

132
00:08:42.688 --> 00:08:44.565
-Uh. do you need a hand?
-I've got it.

133
00:08:47.151 --> 00:08:48.069
I've got it.

134
00:08:48.569 --> 00:08:51.030
Let me. um. take this upstairs for you.

135
00:08:51.113 --> 00:08:52.907
Um…

136
00:08:54.283 --> 00:08:57.203
I didn't know what to text.
so I just came over.

137
00:08:58.704 --> 00:08:59.789
You holding up?

138
00:09:00.581 --> 00:09:01.958
Honestly. I don't know.

139
00:09:04.377 --> 00:09:05.753
It's okay not to know.

140
00:09:08.798 --> 00:09:10.174
That makes me feel better.

141
00:09:10.841 --> 00:09:11.676
Thanks.

142
00:09:14.929 --> 00:09:15.846
Attagirl.

143
00:09:23.229 --> 00:09:25.982
Thank you all for being here.
including the new faces.

144
00:09:26.482 --> 00:09:28.359
Great news for our upcoming art walk.

145
00:09:28.442 --> 00:09:32.363
We'll need all hands to do it right.
Lots of work ahead of us.

146
00:09:32.905 --> 00:09:36.951
But if we all work together.
no question. we can pull it off.

147
00:09:37.034 --> 00:09:39.537
That's not what we're worried about.
We all know what happened

148
00:09:39.620 --> 00:09:40.913
to the Sullivans last night.

149
00:09:40.997 --> 00:09:43.249
and it doesn't feel right
not to talk about it.

150
00:09:43.332 --> 00:09:44.542
Yeah. We'd like to help.

151
00:09:44.625 --> 00:09:46.460
Losing your home is a tragedy.

152
00:09:46.544 --> 00:09:49.463
And with Annie leaving for college soon.
I… I can't imagine.

153
00:09:49.547 --> 00:09:52.341
I was planning on dropping off
some groceries from the co-op.

154
00:09:52.425 --> 00:09:54.552
If folks have things
they'd like to donate.

155
00:09:54.635 --> 00:09:56.512
then I can arrange delivery to Maddie's.

156
00:09:56.596 --> 00:09:59.473
I'm sure they'd appreciate
a care package from loving neighbors.

157
00:09:59.557 --> 00:10:02.727
And I was just at the spa
at The Dewberry in Charleston with Jimmy.

158
00:10:02.810 --> 00:10:06.022
I'll donate all my goodies
so they can pamper themselves.

159
00:10:06.105 --> 00:10:09.150
I doubt they'll need silk scarves.
but I have plenty of linens.

160
00:10:09.233 --> 00:10:10.610
I can donate some quilts.

161
00:10:10.693 --> 00:10:11.777
How about a meal train?

162
00:10:11.861 --> 00:10:13.237
Great idea. Principal Puckett.

163
00:10:13.321 --> 00:10:16.449
-Oh. it's Yvonne. Please.
-Yeah. I'd really love to cook for them.

164
00:10:16.532 --> 00:10:18.743
-Me too.
-This is wonderful.

165
00:10:18.826 --> 00:10:22.413
The original Art Guild
was more of a safe place for women

166
00:10:22.496 --> 00:10:24.582
to gather and help each other quietly.

167
00:10:24.665 --> 00:10:27.043
I feel this Art Guild is gonna be loud.

168
00:10:27.126 --> 00:10:29.670
Thank you for getting us going. Noreen.

169
00:10:30.880 --> 00:10:32.173
Thank you.

170
00:10:33.924 --> 00:10:35.384
-Wonderful.
-Thank you.

171
00:10:40.097 --> 00:10:42.350
Ugh. I am not
in the right frame of mind to shop.

172
00:10:42.433 --> 00:10:45.519
Well. that is why we made an appointment
with Wally himself. Come on.

173
00:10:45.603 --> 00:10:47.355
Yeah. and if you don't comply.

174
00:10:47.438 --> 00:10:51.901
I have Paula on speed dial.
and I will not hesitate to activate her.

175
00:10:51.984 --> 00:10:54.904
You would make me shop
with the woman who sent Maddie to school

176
00:10:54.987 --> 00:10:57.406
in an orange muumuu and teal capris
in seventh grade?

177
00:10:57.490 --> 00:10:59.200
I liked my teal capris.

178
00:11:00.576 --> 00:11:02.787
Fine. Just the essentials.

179
00:11:02.870 --> 00:11:04.872
Oh. let me be of service.

180
00:11:05.790 --> 00:11:07.333
Oh. my lamb.

181
00:11:08.459 --> 00:11:10.378
I am sorry for your misfortune.

182
00:11:10.461 --> 00:11:11.629
-Thank you.
-Hm.

183
00:11:12.880 --> 00:11:14.924
Oh. Wally.

184
00:11:16.092 --> 00:11:20.137
Oh. the colors. the texture. this pattern.

185
00:11:22.181 --> 00:11:25.017
Well. everything you picked out
is absolutely exquisite. Wally.

186
00:11:25.101 --> 00:11:27.311
But I'll have to come back for all of it.
I can't.

187
00:11:27.395 --> 00:11:29.730
Not right now. I just need some slacks.

188
00:11:29.814 --> 00:11:33.943
A beautiful woman like you
does not need just some slacks.

189
00:11:34.568 --> 00:11:36.612
Well… maybe a skirt.

190
00:11:36.696 --> 00:11:39.156
People see me in my finery

191
00:11:39.240 --> 00:11:43.494
and think rigid. restrictive. ritzy.

192
00:11:43.577 --> 00:11:47.081
In actuality.
this is an expression of who I am.

193
00:11:47.164 --> 00:11:50.793
and. darling.
I am God's most breathtaking child.

194
00:11:50.876 --> 00:11:53.754
-Yes. you are.
-But even angels fall.

195
00:11:53.838 --> 00:11:55.715
So this is also armor.

196
00:11:56.340 --> 00:11:58.217
It lends me strength.

197
00:11:59.260 --> 00:12:01.637
A radiance.

198
00:12:02.221 --> 00:12:03.347
Spirit.

199
00:12:03.848 --> 00:12:05.558
Because. my dear.

200
00:12:06.058 --> 00:12:09.854
what is essential is not what you wear.

201
00:12:09.937 --> 00:12:10.813
Hm?

202
00:12:10.896 --> 00:12:12.440
But how you feel.

203
00:12:14.483 --> 00:12:15.609
Take a moment.

204
00:12:18.946 --> 00:12:21.115
I didn't realize it would be so hard
to say no to Wally.

205
00:12:21.198 --> 00:12:22.199
Then don't.

206
00:12:22.283 --> 00:12:24.702
Always say yes to Wally.

207
00:12:24.785 --> 00:12:26.996
These shoes. this suit.

208
00:12:27.079 --> 00:12:29.457
My je ne sais quoi. It's all his doing.

209
00:12:30.040 --> 00:12:31.751
Hm. Find some color.

210
00:12:31.834 --> 00:12:34.211
A little joy
to get you through the rough times.

211
00:12:35.379 --> 00:12:37.465
It's what makes the darkness bearable.

212
00:12:38.966 --> 00:12:42.094
Yeah. but I have so much to take care of.
Annie. Ronnie. the house.

213
00:12:42.178 --> 00:12:44.430
This is what taking care of yourself
looks like.

214
00:12:44.513 --> 00:12:46.724
Especially when the tab is covered.

215
00:12:50.811 --> 00:12:52.521
Say yes to Wally.

216
00:12:54.106 --> 00:12:56.776
Remember. players.
the point of the mirror exercise

217
00:12:56.859 --> 00:12:59.570
is to look like
a reflection of your partner.

218
00:12:59.653 --> 00:13:00.946
Connect with them.

219
00:13:01.572 --> 00:13:04.575
Trust them.
I shouldn't be able to tell who's leading.

220
00:13:06.911 --> 00:13:07.828
Hey.

221
00:13:08.788 --> 00:13:10.039
Trust your girlfriend.

222
00:13:10.122 --> 00:13:11.582
Sorry. I just…

223
00:13:12.166 --> 00:13:14.543
That's not how mirrors work.

224
00:13:14.627 --> 00:13:17.296
-It's not how this exercise works.
-Hey. Wait.

225
00:13:17.379 --> 00:13:18.547
What's the problem here?

226
00:13:18.631 --> 00:13:20.090
She's not taking this seriously.

227
00:13:20.591 --> 00:13:23.803
Since we go to different high schools.
Timothy and I barely know each other.

228
00:13:23.886 --> 00:13:26.263
We're still learning
to trust and respect each other.

229
00:13:26.347 --> 00:13:27.306
I can help you. Lily.

230
00:13:27.389 --> 00:13:29.642
I assumed you were getting
experimental coaching.

231
00:13:29.725 --> 00:13:31.101
Okay. watch it. Timothy.

232
00:13:32.228 --> 00:13:36.023
If Timothy and I work together
with patience and respect.

233
00:13:36.106 --> 00:13:38.234
we can get where we need to be. Max.

234
00:13:39.777 --> 00:13:40.986
Don't you agree. Timothy?

235
00:13:41.070 --> 00:13:42.154
I do.

236
00:13:43.113 --> 00:13:44.281
I really do. Lily.

237
00:13:44.824 --> 00:13:45.991
Can we try it again. Max?

238
00:13:46.659 --> 00:13:49.411
Going again. people. Focus. Come on.

239
00:13:51.163 --> 00:13:53.332
Keep it going. Try something different.

240
00:13:53.415 --> 00:13:56.585
Is it my imagination.
or do you smell the smoke from here?

241
00:13:58.087 --> 00:14:00.673
Maybe a little.
Would you like me to close the window?

242
00:14:00.756 --> 00:14:03.551
Yeah. I can't seem to get away from it.
It's still in my hair.

243
00:14:04.343 --> 00:14:06.512
Did you and Ronnie
get everything out the way you wanted?

244
00:14:07.179 --> 00:14:11.183
Do you ever find yourself
looking for help from an adult

245
00:14:11.267 --> 00:14:13.602
when you're in hot water.
and then you realize.

246
00:14:13.686 --> 00:14:16.313
"Oh no. it's… it's me. I'm the adult"?

247
00:14:19.608 --> 00:14:21.235
I just miss my mom

248
00:14:22.862 --> 00:14:24.613
something fierce.

249
00:14:26.907 --> 00:14:29.869
What would your mom say
if she was sitting with us now?

250
00:14:32.246 --> 00:14:33.831
That she loves me.

251
00:14:35.207 --> 00:14:37.001
That she's here for me.

252
00:14:39.920 --> 00:14:41.005
I love you.

253
00:14:41.505 --> 00:14:42.923
And I am here for you.

254
00:14:43.424 --> 00:14:47.386
♪ Young and overthinking ♪

255
00:14:48.512 --> 00:14:52.391
♪ Coming up on past regret ♪

256
00:14:52.474 --> 00:14:58.814
♪ Whenever I've been sinking
You're always there ♪

257
00:14:58.898 --> 00:15:04.528
♪ You pull away as if you never care ♪

258
00:15:07.239 --> 00:15:12.828
♪ Created distance as my last distrain ♪

259
00:15:13.787 --> 00:15:20.753
♪ I can't move like you do. no. no ♪

260
00:15:21.545 --> 00:15:25.341
♪ So leave me in your dust ♪

261
00:15:25.424 --> 00:15:29.178
♪ And just go ♪

262
00:15:29.970 --> 00:15:36.977
♪ Leave me in your dust ♪

263
00:15:42.483 --> 00:15:43.317
Hey. Noreen.

264
00:15:43.400 --> 00:15:45.444
You're not supposed to be here… yet.

265
00:15:45.527 --> 00:15:47.613
That's the general consensus.

266
00:15:47.696 --> 00:15:50.658
And since
he's disrupted everyone's schedule.

267
00:15:50.741 --> 00:15:52.660
Michael will be babysitting Bex now.

268
00:15:52.743 --> 00:15:54.745
Just kidding. We will babysit together.

269
00:15:56.038 --> 00:15:57.998
Miss Rebecca? Ready?

270
00:15:58.082 --> 00:15:59.541
Come here. sweetie.

271
00:15:59.625 --> 00:16:01.335
There we go.

272
00:16:01.418 --> 00:16:03.295
-Here you go.
-You got it? Okay.

273
00:16:03.379 --> 00:16:05.547
At least somebody's glad to see me.

274
00:16:06.382 --> 00:16:07.675
What's his name?

275
00:16:12.972 --> 00:16:14.390
Michael came ahead of schedule.

276
00:16:14.473 --> 00:16:18.936
I have been working so hard
to be organized and methodical.

277
00:16:19.019 --> 00:16:22.648
and this is how he repays me.
by being impulsive and unpredictable.

278
00:16:22.731 --> 00:16:24.400
Let's take this one step at a time.

279
00:16:24.483 --> 00:16:27.861
How do I shake him loose without being
obvious that that's exactly what I'm doing

280
00:16:27.945 --> 00:16:30.489
so I can prep for tomorrow's
surprise anniversary dinner?

281
00:16:30.572 --> 00:16:33.534
I am fascinated that Michael's
turning out to be the flexible one.

282
00:16:33.617 --> 00:16:35.452
Can I get a rain check

283
00:16:35.536 --> 00:16:39.248
on the loving sarcasm so that we can focus
on the actual problem?

284
00:16:39.331 --> 00:16:41.375
It'll all be fine. I'll help you.

285
00:16:46.588 --> 00:16:47.673
Finished. Chef.

286
00:16:49.425 --> 00:16:51.135
Will this do. Chef?

287
00:16:51.218 --> 00:16:54.638
I said I needed comfort
but not that much comfort.

288
00:16:54.722 --> 00:16:58.475
I almost made pizzas to summon
the joyous spirit of Augusto among us.

289
00:16:58.559 --> 00:17:01.145
but quesadillas go better with margaritas.

290
00:17:01.645 --> 00:17:04.648
We should sneak in here every week
for Margarita Night.

291
00:17:04.732 --> 00:17:08.277
The tequila at Sullivan's and Friends
is much better than anything we purchase.

292
00:17:08.360 --> 00:17:10.612
You better splurge
for margaritas at your wedding.

293
00:17:10.696 --> 00:17:13.574
Otherwise. Dana Sue and I
will be forced to ask Miss Iris

294
00:17:13.657 --> 00:17:16.744
to sew flask-sized pockets
into our bridesmaid dresses.

295
00:17:16.827 --> 00:17:18.245
-Y'all better not.
-Right.

296
00:17:19.788 --> 00:17:24.126
The first time my mom made me quesadillas
with the crispy cheese edges.

297
00:17:24.209 --> 00:17:25.878
I nearly lost my mind.

298
00:17:25.961 --> 00:17:30.049
Mmm. If I recall correctly.
we all lost our minds.

299
00:17:30.132 --> 00:17:33.594
I'm losing my mind right now.
How are you not burning your fingers?

300
00:17:33.677 --> 00:17:35.262
Chef fingers. I'm used to the heat.

301
00:17:35.345 --> 00:17:38.766
But you're gonna wanna let those cool
for a moment.

302
00:17:38.849 --> 00:17:40.059
-Shall we?
-Yes.

303
00:17:40.142 --> 00:17:42.102
-Pour it out.
-Pour it out.

304
00:17:44.313 --> 00:17:45.773
-Mm.
-Mmm.

305
00:17:47.024 --> 00:17:48.942
This is exactly what I needed.

306
00:17:49.026 --> 00:17:51.487
Comfort food in my happy place

307
00:17:51.570 --> 00:17:55.532
with the two people in the world
who can make me feel at home anywhere.

308
00:17:55.616 --> 00:17:57.159
Ah.

309
00:17:57.242 --> 00:18:00.079
Even when surrounded
by insufferable raccoons.

310
00:18:00.162 --> 00:18:03.207
-Think they'll be joining us tonight?
-Better them than Clark.

311
00:18:03.749 --> 00:18:06.585
You know.
I'd be committing perjury if I didn't say

312
00:18:06.668 --> 00:18:10.798
I wasn't frustrated by the way
things panned out with the Bellwether.

313
00:18:10.881 --> 00:18:13.342
Especially since
I finally figured out my portion.

314
00:18:13.425 --> 00:18:15.344
Well. you've kept us waiting long enough.

315
00:18:15.427 --> 00:18:17.387
Yeah. we're all ears.

316
00:18:17.888 --> 00:18:20.432
Noreen renewed
my friendship with Miss Eustice.

317
00:18:20.516 --> 00:18:23.143
which led to the revival of the Art Guild.

318
00:18:23.727 --> 00:18:26.188
Being with all these creative souls

319
00:18:26.271 --> 00:18:28.857
and thinking of all the joy
that it brought to Serenity

320
00:18:28.941 --> 00:18:30.943
when my mom and Miss Eustice were young.

321
00:18:31.026 --> 00:18:32.778
it's been inspiring.

322
00:18:32.861 --> 00:18:34.404
So.

323
00:18:35.114 --> 00:18:38.033
I wanna dedicate my portion

324
00:18:38.575 --> 00:18:41.286
to an art gallery and artists' workshop.

325
00:18:41.370 --> 00:18:43.163
-Oh.
-I know.

326
00:18:43.247 --> 00:18:46.375
Up those creaky stairs.

327
00:18:46.458 --> 00:18:52.214
Behold. a… a breeze wafts
through organza curtains

328
00:18:52.297 --> 00:18:56.844
and across polished hardwood floors.

329
00:18:57.678 --> 00:19:00.931
Deep amber shafts of sunlight.

330
00:19:04.935 --> 00:19:05.769
Divine.

331
00:19:06.270 --> 00:19:08.814
Well. you just painted a picture.

332
00:19:08.897 --> 00:19:11.900
-It's a beautiful idea.
-I wager my mom will be your first client.

333
00:19:11.984 --> 00:19:15.821
I am so excited.
I even told Erik about it the other day.

334
00:19:16.321 --> 00:19:19.116
A little distraction
from all the wedding planning woes.

335
00:19:19.199 --> 00:19:21.410
Woes? Is there something
we could be helping you with?

336
00:19:21.493 --> 00:19:24.663
More discussion
than decisions at the moment. but

337
00:19:25.664 --> 00:19:26.707
we'll figure it out.

338
00:19:26.790 --> 00:19:28.417
Ronnie doesn't even know yet.

339
00:19:28.500 --> 00:19:31.920
I was about to tell him. then…
And how can I tell him now?

340
00:19:32.421 --> 00:19:34.923
I do not have the energy
for the discussion

341
00:19:35.007 --> 00:19:36.508
that is surely to follow.

342
00:19:37.092 --> 00:19:40.179
I don't even have the energy
to judge the chili cook-off.

343
00:19:40.262 --> 00:19:42.890
It's my favorite part of Fourth of July.

344
00:19:42.973 --> 00:19:44.975
You're not judging?

345
00:19:45.058 --> 00:19:47.603
Then this is the year that I enter.

346
00:19:47.686 --> 00:19:48.937
Stick with snow cones.

347
00:19:53.483 --> 00:19:56.695
We will find a new place.
Who knows? Maybe it'll find us.

348
00:19:57.196 --> 00:19:58.947
I would very much like

349
00:19:59.489 --> 00:20:00.782
good news to find me.

350
00:20:00.866 --> 00:20:03.785
As much as we would like life
to be a smooth path.

351
00:20:03.869 --> 00:20:07.206
it's like peaks and… and valleys.

352
00:20:07.289 --> 00:20:10.500
and even rabbit holes appear suddenly.

353
00:20:10.584 --> 00:20:15.297
The ground can even shift
and open at your feet.

354
00:20:15.881 --> 00:20:17.758
And it's up to us to hold on.

355
00:20:17.841 --> 00:20:20.719
Hold on to each other and persevere.

356
00:20:20.802 --> 00:20:24.097
Look at the peaks you've already scaled
and the valleys you've crossed.

357
00:20:24.181 --> 00:20:25.766
Hm.

358
00:20:25.849 --> 00:20:26.683
More raccoons?

359
00:20:26.767 --> 00:20:27.893
Where'd I go wrong?

360
00:20:28.727 --> 00:20:31.605
Am I not allowed to have
all the things I want at the same time?

361
00:20:31.688 --> 00:20:35.108
Do I have to lose something
to gain something else?

362
00:20:37.903 --> 00:20:41.615
And… and now I'm holding you two back
from pursuing your dreams.

363
00:20:41.698 --> 00:20:43.408
What on earth are you talking about?

364
00:20:43.492 --> 00:20:46.954
I'm gonna stumble…
and pull you down the mountain.

365
00:20:48.455 --> 00:20:51.667
-You should move forward without me.
-Don't you dare. Dana Sue!

366
00:20:51.750 --> 00:20:55.963
We are not gonna let you lose sight
of your goal. Fire and Clark be damned!

367
00:20:56.046 --> 00:20:58.548
We have seen each other
through so many valleys.

368
00:20:58.632 --> 00:21:00.592
Helen and I will see you through this one.

369
00:21:00.676 --> 00:21:01.802
Dana Sue.

370
00:21:03.303 --> 00:21:05.931
When you get tired.
you draw on our strength.

371
00:21:06.014 --> 00:21:08.392
And that peak. that view at the top.

372
00:21:08.475 --> 00:21:11.436
it is going to be sublime.

373
00:21:12.604 --> 00:21:13.730
Because we…

374
00:21:16.233 --> 00:21:17.943
we will have scaled it together.

375
00:21:26.910 --> 00:21:30.247
The rec department swim program
was canceled after the water main break.

376
00:21:30.330 --> 00:21:32.874
but the proceeds
from the tickets and baseball cards

377
00:21:32.958 --> 00:21:36.503
we sold at the alumni game
were able to help reinstate it.

378
00:21:36.586 --> 00:21:40.090
Just one example
of how this new team and the tourism

379
00:21:40.173 --> 00:21:43.218
that will inevitably follow
could generate revenue.

380
00:21:43.302 --> 00:21:45.679
All without the overhead of an MLB team.

381
00:21:46.346 --> 00:21:48.557
So perfect for a town like ours.

382
00:21:50.642 --> 00:21:53.562
That's an attractive idea worth exploring.

383
00:21:53.645 --> 00:21:55.522
But not without risks.

384
00:21:55.605 --> 00:21:58.859
Unfortunately.
this isn't solely my decision to make.

385
00:22:00.444 --> 00:22:01.403
I love baseball.

386
00:22:04.406 --> 00:22:05.949
I'll put you on the agenda.

387
00:22:06.033 --> 00:22:07.326
But be forewarned.

388
00:22:07.409 --> 00:22:11.371
town council is a tough bunch.
especially when it comes to the budget.

389
00:22:11.455 --> 00:22:13.165
While there will be money rolling in.

390
00:22:13.248 --> 00:22:19.129
it'll be a minute before we get our return
on anything we lay out. including tourism.

391
00:22:19.212 --> 00:22:22.257
-Does Serenity have a tourism board?
-You might be starting one.

392
00:22:22.341 --> 00:22:25.093
That would be a good way
to show the council

393
00:22:25.177 --> 00:22:27.971
that there are enough sponsors in town

394
00:22:28.055 --> 00:22:30.891
who are willing to put their weight
and resources behind this.

395
00:22:30.974 --> 00:22:32.517
Okay. sure.

396
00:22:32.601 --> 00:22:34.686
They'll also want to know about lodging.

397
00:22:34.770 --> 00:22:37.397
food and beverage.
entertainment. and transpo.

398
00:22:37.481 --> 00:22:40.150
Answer those questions thoroughly.

399
00:22:40.692 --> 00:22:44.946
and you might very well
have yourself a baseball team.

400
00:22:46.990 --> 00:22:49.993
Thank you for going to bat for me. Mayor.
You won't regret it.

401
00:22:50.077 --> 00:22:51.536
I look forward to your proposal.

402
00:22:52.788 --> 00:22:55.082
Uh. you forgot your baseball cards.

403
00:22:55.582 --> 00:22:57.167
Oh. those are for the two of you.

404
00:22:57.667 --> 00:23:00.045
By the way. Neville's is the most popular.

405
00:23:09.513 --> 00:23:11.556
We get our coffee beans
from a local roaster

406
00:23:11.640 --> 00:23:12.974
I met at the farmer's market.

407
00:23:13.058 --> 00:23:17.979
And it was my idea to use a rotating staff
to run the bar. which Annie is a part of.

408
00:23:18.063 --> 00:23:21.358
I'm sad I'll miss all the work
Isaac will be doing while I'm at school.

409
00:23:21.441 --> 00:23:23.652
I could come regularly
just to get you an update.

410
00:23:23.735 --> 00:23:26.446
I might take you up on that.
or at least someone might.

411
00:23:29.991 --> 00:23:31.952
-Hey.
-Noah.

412
00:23:32.494 --> 00:23:34.663
Hi. how can I help you?

413
00:23:34.746 --> 00:23:36.123
Your bandanna.

414
00:23:36.206 --> 00:23:39.042
I'm… I'm not sure it survived the fire.

415
00:23:39.126 --> 00:23:42.003
Oh. not to worry.
I mean. there's more where that came from.

416
00:23:42.879 --> 00:23:46.550
No. I'm… I'm so sorry.
That sounded smarmy. I did not intend--

417
00:23:46.633 --> 00:23:48.176
Don't worry. I got it.

418
00:23:48.760 --> 00:23:51.179
Papa and Grandma told me what happened.

419
00:23:52.180 --> 00:23:55.183
Is there anything I can do for you?
Is your family okay?

420
00:23:57.060 --> 00:23:58.145
Um…

421
00:23:59.062 --> 00:24:00.147
I'm okay.

422
00:24:00.230 --> 00:24:02.065
All things considered.

423
00:24:02.816 --> 00:24:04.484
Work's been a great distraction.

424
00:24:05.068 --> 00:24:08.447
And I shouldn't distract you from work.
I just wanted to check in.

425
00:24:08.530 --> 00:24:09.614
You came all this way.

426
00:24:09.698 --> 00:24:12.659
and you're not gonna try
one of Isaac's amazing coffees?

427
00:24:14.035 --> 00:24:15.287
Anything you recommend?

428
00:24:15.370 --> 00:24:18.206
I hear the Annie is super…

429
00:24:19.499 --> 00:24:20.500
super.

430
00:24:21.668 --> 00:24:24.838
Okay. The Annie sounds perfect.
I'll have that.

431
00:24:32.137 --> 00:24:33.388
What is this?

432
00:24:33.472 --> 00:24:34.473
The Michael.

433
00:24:34.556 --> 00:24:37.809
Cold brew concentrate. tonic.
and house-made cherry juice.

434
00:24:37.893 --> 00:24:40.061
Intense. refreshing.

435
00:24:43.106 --> 00:24:46.651
How did you come up with the recipe?
I… I've never had anything like this.

436
00:24:46.735 --> 00:24:49.571
It was sudden inspiration.

437
00:24:49.654 --> 00:24:52.032
After 14 previous attempts.

438
00:24:55.118 --> 00:24:57.412
-I love--
-Of course. these are seasonal flavors.

439
00:24:57.496 --> 00:25:00.457
So we can keep experimenting.

440
00:25:00.540 --> 00:25:02.250
No need. I… I love--

441
00:25:02.334 --> 00:25:06.338
Would you love a pecan tart?
Let me get you a pecan tart.

442
00:25:14.012 --> 00:25:14.930
What you working on?

443
00:25:15.013 --> 00:25:20.143
I know that we don't have
a physical space yet. but

444
00:25:20.727 --> 00:25:22.312
I am moving forward in faith

445
00:25:22.395 --> 00:25:24.856
and crafting
a mission statement for my bookshop.

446
00:25:24.940 --> 00:25:25.982
So manifesting.

447
00:25:26.483 --> 00:25:27.734
Judging by that grin.

448
00:25:27.817 --> 00:25:30.362
I take it the meeting
with Peggy and Henrietta went well?

449
00:25:30.445 --> 00:25:32.531
I'm on the town council agenda.

450
00:25:33.156 --> 00:25:35.116
-Well. that's great news.
-Yeah.

451
00:25:35.200 --> 00:25:37.827
Okay. So why am I sensing
an incoming "but"?

452
00:25:37.911 --> 00:25:41.373
But I basically have to put together
a tourism board.

453
00:25:41.456 --> 00:25:42.582
How do I do that?

454
00:25:42.666 --> 00:25:45.794
I'm a ball player. not a bureaucrat.

455
00:25:45.877 --> 00:25:47.921
Well. I'm not a bureaucrat either.

456
00:25:48.004 --> 00:25:52.676
but I always feel like it helps
to tell people a story.

457
00:25:54.010 --> 00:25:56.096
Okay. Work with me here.

458
00:25:56.179 --> 00:26:00.684
Tell me a story about…
your love for baseball

459
00:26:01.184 --> 00:26:02.102
and this town.

460
00:26:06.022 --> 00:26:08.024
I love

461
00:26:09.276 --> 00:26:12.237
that baseball brings people together.

462
00:26:14.531 --> 00:26:16.491
At practice and the game.

463
00:26:16.992 --> 00:26:19.160
In the stands and on the field.

464
00:26:21.538 --> 00:26:25.292
Being here helped me understand that.

465
00:26:25.375 --> 00:26:27.002
And… and. like Serenity.

466
00:26:27.085 --> 00:26:31.631
baseball works best
when people respect each other's strengths

467
00:26:32.132 --> 00:26:35.969
and celebrate the wins
and learn from the losses.

468
00:26:36.052 --> 00:26:37.596
And I think

469
00:26:38.680 --> 00:26:40.557
that the town I love…

470
00:26:42.767 --> 00:26:44.269
will love the sport I love.

471
00:26:49.107 --> 00:26:50.442
Did I make you sad?

472
00:26:52.152 --> 00:26:53.486
The exact opposite.

473
00:26:55.530 --> 00:26:57.866
You are a gift.

474
00:27:04.497 --> 00:27:05.665
Hi.

475
00:27:07.375 --> 00:27:08.835
-Hey.
-Hey.

476
00:27:08.918 --> 00:27:11.171
I thought you had errands
to run for Aunt Helen.

477
00:27:11.254 --> 00:27:14.174
I'm almost done.
so I thought I'd stop by for a coffee.

478
00:27:14.257 --> 00:27:17.302
You're an iced coffee. black. right?

479
00:27:17.385 --> 00:27:20.180
Yeah. actually. Thanks.

480
00:27:21.973 --> 00:27:24.559
Is there anything
I could be doing for you?

481
00:27:24.643 --> 00:27:26.394
Errands or at home?

482
00:27:26.478 --> 00:27:28.647
Whispering to my uncle
that you need time off?

483
00:27:28.730 --> 00:27:31.775
Thanks. but he already asked.

484
00:27:31.858 --> 00:27:36.154
and it feels really good
to be here focusing on other people.

485
00:27:37.197 --> 00:27:40.408
Plus. it's nice to see friends at work.

486
00:27:42.577 --> 00:27:43.411
Thanks.

487
00:27:59.052 --> 00:28:00.053
Jessica.

488
00:28:01.596 --> 00:28:02.806
Did you need something?

489
00:28:03.723 --> 00:28:04.557
I'm fine.

490
00:28:05.558 --> 00:28:06.601
But…

491
00:28:08.103 --> 00:28:12.148
…I'm concerned that things need to be
smoothed over between you and Miss Helen.

492
00:28:15.068 --> 00:28:17.904
That is inappropriate and unlike you.

493
00:28:18.738 --> 00:28:20.156
Please talk to her.

494
00:28:20.240 --> 00:28:23.326
Otherwise. you could end up losing
what Mom and Dad lost.

495
00:28:23.410 --> 00:28:26.871
Please. Uncle Erik. before it's too late.

496
00:28:26.955 --> 00:28:29.582
What goes on between adults
is not for you to speak on.

497
00:28:29.666 --> 00:28:31.000
You're impossible.

498
00:28:31.668 --> 00:28:35.380
Just like Dad and Grandfather.
and poor Helen has no idea.

499
00:28:35.463 --> 00:28:38.925
To think that I came here
because I imagined you'd be different.

500
00:28:39.634 --> 00:28:42.178
But I was wrong
about my parents and their marriage.

501
00:28:42.262 --> 00:28:44.389
So why would I be right about you?

502
00:28:44.472 --> 00:28:45.640
Young lady--

503
00:28:45.724 --> 00:28:49.394
If your house went up in flames.
all you'd grab is the Whitley way.

504
00:28:57.736 --> 00:29:00.488
Thank you for sharing
so much of your technique with me.

505
00:29:00.572 --> 00:29:02.532
It's really instructive.

506
00:29:02.615 --> 00:29:04.659
Kyle's not the only one
with memorable moves.

507
00:29:05.660 --> 00:29:07.620
It's important
to learn multiple techniques

508
00:29:07.704 --> 00:29:09.581
then decide which one works best for you.

509
00:29:10.081 --> 00:29:11.875
I appreciate you both.

510
00:29:11.958 --> 00:29:13.293
And I appreciate you.

511
00:29:16.838 --> 00:29:17.672
Kyle.

512
00:29:26.306 --> 00:29:28.975
I like acting
because I like entertaining people.

513
00:29:29.058 --> 00:29:30.310
making them think.

514
00:29:31.644 --> 00:29:34.397
But I suspect Timothy's in this
for a whole different reason.

515
00:29:35.023 --> 00:29:36.649
I still need to figure that out.

516
00:29:38.067 --> 00:29:40.236
To help him be a better actor?

517
00:29:42.822 --> 00:29:45.492
To help me be
a better presence in his life.

518
00:29:47.994 --> 00:29:49.496
Have you figured me out?

519
00:29:51.706 --> 00:29:52.832
You are deep

520
00:29:53.374 --> 00:29:54.542
and profound.

521
00:29:54.626 --> 00:29:58.546
and I just wanna
keep learning more about you every day.

522
00:29:59.756 --> 00:30:01.633
To help me be a better actor?

523
00:30:02.175 --> 00:30:05.386
To help me love you the way you deserve.

524
00:30:06.137 --> 00:30:07.263
Good answer.

525
00:30:18.858 --> 00:30:20.109
We need to talk.

526
00:30:21.694 --> 00:30:23.655
Things have changed between us.

527
00:30:24.739 --> 00:30:28.785
But the ground beneath your feet
has shifted. and you need to leave.

528
00:30:30.787 --> 00:30:31.663
Go.

529
00:30:33.748 --> 00:30:35.708
I'm shocked you would even think that.

530
00:30:36.209 --> 00:30:37.877
I've been trying so hard to hold on.

531
00:30:37.961 --> 00:30:41.756
Yeah. and I have been trying
to give you something to hold on to.

532
00:30:41.840 --> 00:30:44.217
but you seem determined
to cling to something else.

533
00:30:44.300 --> 00:30:46.511
I was clinging to the symbols
of my parents' marriage.

534
00:30:46.594 --> 00:30:49.222
-Despite the toll on ours?
-I was trying to protect us.

535
00:30:49.305 --> 00:30:50.473
By surrendering.

536
00:30:50.557 --> 00:30:54.227
I realize I was trying to please others
when I should have been pleasing you.

537
00:30:54.310 --> 00:30:56.980
Because that is what
I'm dedicating my life to.

538
00:30:57.063 --> 00:30:59.983
Because this is what ignites my soul.

539
00:31:00.066 --> 00:31:03.862
Because if this house were on fire.
the only thing that I would grab is you.

540
00:31:05.321 --> 00:31:06.656
Well. then grab me.

541
00:31:30.346 --> 00:31:32.265
This was a brilliant idea. Noreen.

542
00:31:32.348 --> 00:31:34.767
Thank you for suggesting
we move the dinner here.

543
00:31:34.851 --> 00:31:39.147
I know I can be a little theatrical.
but this moment deserves it.

544
00:31:39.647 --> 00:31:42.317
I don't know what I would've done
without your help.

545
00:31:42.400 --> 00:31:47.196
Planning and replanning the…
Champagne. Did I not grab the Sangiovese?

546
00:31:47.697 --> 00:31:52.160
The champagne is a gift from Jeremy.
and I also have a gift for you.

547
00:31:52.243 --> 00:31:53.703
Live music for tonight.

548
00:31:54.287 --> 00:31:57.707
So you won't need that hideous boom box
I saw Kyle lug in.

549
00:32:03.171 --> 00:32:04.881
-Yeah.
-Great. thank you.

550
00:32:04.964 --> 00:32:05.882
Noreen.

551
00:32:05.965 --> 00:32:07.592
Hush. it's the least I could do.

552
00:32:08.092 --> 00:32:11.554
Jeremy and I had so much fun
at our faux date because of you.

553
00:32:12.680 --> 00:32:14.140
This is Michael.

554
00:32:15.391 --> 00:32:17.185
Have a wonderful evening. I love you.

555
00:32:17.268 --> 00:32:18.144
Love you.

556
00:32:19.395 --> 00:32:21.898
Commence Operation Anniversary Dinner.

557
00:32:22.815 --> 00:32:24.943
-Buona sera. signore.
-Buona sera. signore.

558
00:32:25.443 --> 00:32:27.695
Grazie. che bello.

559
00:32:30.615 --> 00:32:31.824
Che bello.

560
00:32:35.662 --> 00:32:36.496
Grazie.

561
00:32:38.206 --> 00:32:40.166
I guess I'm not the only one
with surprises.

562
00:32:40.249 --> 00:32:41.709
What is all this for?

563
00:32:41.793 --> 00:32:45.338
Everyone will attest that I have been
planning this moment since you left.

564
00:32:45.421 --> 00:32:47.507
I have been through so many iterations.

565
00:32:47.590 --> 00:32:49.634
Ah. hence "The Michael."

566
00:32:49.717 --> 00:32:51.511
But nothing felt quite right

567
00:32:51.594 --> 00:32:55.139
until I realized that I needed to do
what I was scared to do.

568
00:32:55.723 --> 00:32:58.184
Share how I feel. So I went for it.

569
00:32:59.185 --> 00:33:00.770
And before you say anything.

570
00:33:01.604 --> 00:33:02.647
let me say.

571
00:33:03.815 --> 00:33:04.774
I love you.

572
00:33:06.234 --> 00:33:08.152
-I'm sorry. what was that?
-I love you.

573
00:33:08.236 --> 00:33:11.572
Any chance
I could get you to say it again?

574
00:33:11.656 --> 00:33:14.075
Over and over and over.

575
00:33:16.911 --> 00:33:18.121
I love you too.

576
00:33:20.957 --> 00:33:23.876
For our antipasta. bruschetta.

577
00:33:25.503 --> 00:33:29.590
You know. I'm not much for hubbub.
but after this red carpet rollout.

578
00:33:30.091 --> 00:33:31.801
I think I should visit more often.

579
00:33:31.884 --> 00:33:33.720
You could stay longer.

580
00:33:34.637 --> 00:33:35.930
Or I could stay longer.

581
00:33:46.858 --> 00:33:48.317
May I have this dance?

582
00:33:49.152 --> 00:33:50.486
You may have them all.

583
00:33:59.287 --> 00:34:02.373
♪ The very thought of you ♪

584
00:34:04.292 --> 00:34:07.879
♪ And I forget to do ♪

585
00:34:09.797 --> 00:34:15.511
♪ The little ordinary things ♪

586
00:34:16.095 --> 00:34:19.223
♪ That everyone ought to do ♪

587
00:34:19.307 --> 00:34:20.224
-I…
-How…

588
00:34:21.768 --> 00:34:22.852
Please.

589
00:34:23.478 --> 00:34:24.395
How what?

590
00:34:26.689 --> 00:34:29.108
How did we get so far off course?

591
00:34:29.192 --> 00:34:30.902
This was supposed to be a…

592
00:34:33.154 --> 00:34:34.447
A fairy tale.

593
00:34:35.656 --> 00:34:38.367
But instead of the prince.
I've been the ogre.

594
00:34:38.451 --> 00:34:40.787
But I don't believe in fairy tales.

595
00:34:42.830 --> 00:34:44.707
I believe in telling the truth.

596
00:34:47.001 --> 00:34:48.252
And yet…

597
00:34:51.255 --> 00:34:54.759
yet I feel like there's some truths
that you're still not telling me.

598
00:34:59.764 --> 00:35:01.974
Hey. No. don't.

599
00:35:03.935 --> 00:35:05.603
Don't turn away from me.

600
00:35:15.071 --> 00:35:17.532
My parents didn't like Vera.

601
00:35:18.741 --> 00:35:19.700
What?

602
00:35:21.619 --> 00:35:22.995
When I lost her.

603
00:35:23.746 --> 00:35:25.123
I felt I mourned alone.

604
00:35:25.706 --> 00:35:27.041
Oh. Erik.

605
00:35:27.625 --> 00:35:30.294
They found her… willful.

606
00:35:31.504 --> 00:35:32.505
driven.

607
00:35:33.840 --> 00:35:35.049
and too independent.

608
00:35:35.133 --> 00:35:36.717
Oh dear.

609
00:35:36.801 --> 00:35:40.012
What she was was passionate. committed.

610
00:35:41.055 --> 00:35:42.890
and unafraid to speak her mind.

611
00:35:49.480 --> 00:35:51.941
I do not love you
because you are like her.

612
00:35:52.024 --> 00:35:57.155
I love you because you are a unique.
complex. fascinating woman

613
00:35:57.238 --> 00:36:00.491
with your own beautiful mix
of gifts and graces.

614
00:36:01.242 --> 00:36:05.121
My parents like you very much.
and they will grow to love you.

615
00:36:05.621 --> 00:36:06.622
I'm certain.

616
00:36:07.915 --> 00:36:12.128
I just let past fear and pain

617
00:36:12.211 --> 00:36:15.673
focus me on removing
every potential bump in that road.

618
00:36:15.756 --> 00:36:18.259
And I lost sight of where that road leads.

619
00:36:19.218 --> 00:36:20.052
Our wedding.

620
00:36:20.761 --> 00:36:22.847
Our marriage. Our future.

621
00:36:23.723 --> 00:36:25.433
I'm so sorry to have done that to us.

622
00:36:26.350 --> 00:36:27.268
To you.

623
00:36:29.937 --> 00:36:32.648
You could've trusted me with this
a long time ago.

624
00:36:33.441 --> 00:36:36.319
I didn't understand what I was doing
until our visitor arrived.

625
00:36:36.402 --> 00:36:37.361
Jessica?

626
00:36:38.654 --> 00:36:41.741
I see her struggling against
the Whitley way. just as I did.

627
00:36:41.824 --> 00:36:43.701
Even before I met Vera.

628
00:36:43.784 --> 00:36:45.786
In wishing freedom for Jess.

629
00:36:47.121 --> 00:36:50.708
I can see I was binding myself
all over again.

630
00:36:51.459 --> 00:36:53.085
I'll be unpacking this for a while.

631
00:36:53.169 --> 00:36:55.963
No. please. please.

632
00:36:56.047 --> 00:36:57.840
May we unpack it together?

633
00:36:59.175 --> 00:37:01.385
I wanna understand all of it.

634
00:37:02.720 --> 00:37:06.807
I want our journey to be
as joyful as it can be.

635
00:37:07.934 --> 00:37:09.727
I believe what you believe.

636
00:37:10.269 --> 00:37:11.229
What we believe.

637
00:37:12.021 --> 00:37:13.022
This.

638
00:37:13.522 --> 00:37:15.816
Us. and I'll make you a vow.

639
00:37:16.317 --> 00:37:18.194
Right here and now.

640
00:37:19.403 --> 00:37:23.908
I swear to talk more freely
and openly about everything.

641
00:37:23.991 --> 00:37:25.785
From our wedding to

642
00:37:27.203 --> 00:37:29.288
the brand of toothpaste we buy.

643
00:37:32.083 --> 00:37:34.252
Oh. we're gonna get into
the truly deep stuff.

644
00:37:34.335 --> 00:37:35.378
Mm-hmm.

645
00:37:37.672 --> 00:37:40.925
I'm grateful to my parents for so much.

646
00:37:41.008 --> 00:37:43.052
I'm also grateful for Serenity.

647
00:37:43.886 --> 00:37:45.221
But most of all…

648
00:37:48.766 --> 00:37:49.976
I'm grateful to you.

649
00:37:51.602 --> 00:37:54.397
I wanna braid
everything precious I've learned

650
00:37:54.480 --> 00:37:57.316
into a rope we can grab onto

651
00:37:57.400 --> 00:37:59.527
whenever we fear we're losing our way.

652
00:38:00.111 --> 00:38:01.737
One that will bind us

653
00:38:02.863 --> 00:38:05.408
so your beating heart
is always next to mine.

654
00:38:05.908 --> 00:38:09.829
Please forgive me. as I strive to be
the man you fell in love with.

655
00:38:09.912 --> 00:38:10.913
No.

656
00:38:13.416 --> 00:38:16.502
We… will strive together.

657
00:38:32.893 --> 00:38:33.728
What?

658
00:38:36.772 --> 00:38:39.692
It's Jeremy. Courtney no-showed.

659
00:38:40.192 --> 00:38:43.863
She's supposed to help run the Bike Barn
booth for the Fourth of July fair.

660
00:38:43.946 --> 00:38:44.780
which means--

661
00:38:44.864 --> 00:38:47.408
You need to go help him.
like a good partner.

662
00:38:48.034 --> 00:38:49.076
Of course.

663
00:38:58.753 --> 00:38:59.920
Leif.

664
00:39:01.005 --> 00:39:02.882
Do you have an update on our house?

665
00:39:02.965 --> 00:39:04.216
Oh. no. ma'am.

666
00:39:04.759 --> 00:39:09.055
Didn't mean to alarm you.
This is more of a department-wide issue.

667
00:39:10.139 --> 00:39:11.057
How so?

668
00:39:11.140 --> 00:39:14.185
On behalf
of the Serenity Volunteer Fire Department.

669
00:39:14.268 --> 00:39:17.938
I present to you our humble submission
to the Fourth of July chili cook-off.

670
00:39:19.190 --> 00:39:20.649
So sweet.

671
00:39:21.442 --> 00:39:22.401
Got to go.

672
00:39:22.485 --> 00:39:26.072
If it makes a difference.
my sister chopped all the onions.

673
00:39:26.155 --> 00:39:28.783
Yes. Chef. I chopped all the onions.

674
00:39:28.866 --> 00:39:31.243
How wonderful.
but you two must not have heard.

675
00:39:31.327 --> 00:39:33.954
I had to withdraw
from judging the chili cook-off.

676
00:39:34.038 --> 00:39:38.167
Yes. ma'am. We heard.
but… whenever Serenity's in a spot.

677
00:39:38.250 --> 00:39:41.754
you always make chili for us firefighters.
and it's the best ever.

678
00:39:41.837 --> 00:39:44.840
So your opinion
is the only one we care about.

679
00:39:44.924 --> 00:39:47.718
Besides. the win doesn't mean anything
if someone else awards it.

680
00:39:47.802 --> 00:39:49.428
You judge the cook-off every year.

681
00:39:49.512 --> 00:39:52.765
I will taste. but not judge. your chili.

682
00:39:52.848 --> 00:39:54.350
-All right!
-Whoo!

683
00:39:54.433 --> 00:39:55.684
Wait.

684
00:39:55.768 --> 00:39:57.144
Oh. Deputy.

685
00:39:57.228 --> 00:40:00.815
If Dana Sue's judging your chili.
she has to judge ours too.

686
00:40:00.898 --> 00:40:02.983
Not before she tries mine.

687
00:40:06.153 --> 00:40:08.781
I'm sure Helen and Erik
are going through something.

688
00:40:08.864 --> 00:40:10.699
but she won't open up about it.

689
00:40:10.783 --> 00:40:12.910
Dana Sue is obviously devastated

690
00:40:12.993 --> 00:40:15.371
by what can only be described
as a catastrophe. and…

691
00:40:17.540 --> 00:40:18.499
I'm happy.

692
00:40:18.582 --> 00:40:21.752
-You say that like it's a bad thing.
-It is.

693
00:40:21.836 --> 00:40:24.130
How can I be happy when my friends aren't?

694
00:40:27.508 --> 00:40:30.469
You're the light
at the end of their tunnel.

695
00:40:32.012 --> 00:40:34.515
If you were all unhappy.
everyone would be lost.

696
00:40:34.598 --> 00:40:37.101
I don't wanna seem selfish
by saying we'll get through this

697
00:40:37.184 --> 00:40:38.644
when they're both struggling.

698
00:40:38.727 --> 00:40:43.357
Have I promised
to conquer a peak we can't all scale?

699
00:40:43.441 --> 00:40:46.569
You can take a break from climbing
if now's not a good time.

700
00:40:48.195 --> 00:40:50.364
Are you looking for permission to pause?

701
00:40:57.621 --> 00:40:59.415
Do I even wanna know?

702
00:41:15.431 --> 00:41:18.851
And always add a little something
to make the recipe really special.

703
00:41:19.810 --> 00:41:21.604
What is that little something?

704
00:41:21.687 --> 00:41:23.063
That's for you to figure out.

705
00:41:23.147 --> 00:41:24.064
Okay.

706
00:41:25.483 --> 00:41:26.442
Oh.

707
00:41:27.109 --> 00:41:30.779
What a soul. He's a carbon copy
of Willow. just older and taller.

708
00:41:30.863 --> 00:41:33.240
I thought people had to run away
to the circus.

709
00:41:33.741 --> 00:41:37.203
What should we expect next.
a petting zoo erupting in our backyard?

710
00:41:37.286 --> 00:41:38.120
Yeah.

711
00:41:38.204 --> 00:41:41.081
I got some pop-ups
and folding chairs in the garage.

712
00:41:42.208 --> 00:41:43.918
Who's ready to walk off
two bowls of chili?

713
00:41:44.001 --> 00:41:45.878
-Ooh.
-I haven't even had one yet.

714
00:41:45.961 --> 00:41:48.464
You didn't hear it from me.
but you can skip the Bridge Club.

715
00:41:48.547 --> 00:41:49.507
Oh.

716
00:41:49.590 --> 00:41:51.467
Wow. this is quite the party.

717
00:41:51.550 --> 00:41:53.260
Mm. Clark.

718
00:41:53.344 --> 00:41:54.970
So nice of you to drop by.

719
00:41:55.054 --> 00:41:56.764
I didn't know you made chili.

720
00:41:56.847 --> 00:41:59.517
I don't.
but when I saw the great chili exodus

721
00:41:59.600 --> 00:42:02.394
from town square.
yeah. I had to tag along.

722
00:42:02.478 --> 00:42:05.397
It might be the first time in history
the cook-off has relocated.

723
00:42:05.481 --> 00:42:07.900
I understand the drive
to go to the ends of the Earth.

724
00:42:07.983 --> 00:42:09.944
or six blocks. to have Dana Sue judge…

725
00:42:10.027 --> 00:42:10.986
No. taste.

726
00:42:11.070 --> 00:42:12.404
…what they have to offer.

727
00:42:13.030 --> 00:42:15.324
People thrive on traditions they cherish.

728
00:42:15.407 --> 00:42:17.576
Otherwise.
you're just repeating empty rituals

729
00:42:17.660 --> 00:42:19.245
that have lost their meaning.

730
00:42:20.079 --> 00:42:21.497
You save what you love.

731
00:42:22.623 --> 00:42:24.959
Bellsons are raised
to shepherd the community.

732
00:42:25.042 --> 00:42:26.961
and my failure at that gnaws at me

733
00:42:27.044 --> 00:42:30.089
like one of those damn raccoons
chewing on the eaves.

734
00:42:30.965 --> 00:42:32.675
I let Pop's legacy become empty.

735
00:42:32.758 --> 00:42:35.135
We never meant
to make you feel that way. Clark.

736
00:42:35.219 --> 00:42:38.222
I appreciate that. Maddie. I do.
But I own my shortcomings.

737
00:42:39.974 --> 00:42:42.726
You three are the true bellwethers now.

738
00:42:42.810 --> 00:42:44.645
I see your flock.

739
00:42:44.728 --> 00:42:47.314
You Magnolias do
a fine job tending to them.

740
00:42:48.816 --> 00:42:51.360
So I find that I am in search
of a second chance.

741
00:42:51.443 --> 00:42:55.698
and rather than kicking myself
and envying you. I'd like to help out.

742
00:42:55.781 --> 00:42:57.950
Do something my family can be proud of.

743
00:42:58.993 --> 00:43:00.619
Clark. what are you saying?

744
00:43:00.703 --> 00:43:04.748
I will accept your offer
on the Bellwether. with one modification.

745
00:43:04.832 --> 00:43:07.167
-How much higher is the new price?
-No change.

746
00:43:07.751 --> 00:43:10.629
But I retain 20%.
and I partner with the three of you

747
00:43:10.713 --> 00:43:12.214
on a consulting basis.

748
00:43:15.384 --> 00:43:18.345
I'll go sample some chili
while you take some time to think.

749
00:43:19.263 --> 00:43:20.889
Uh. skip the Bridge Club.

750
00:43:23.475 --> 00:43:24.351
Hmm.

751
00:43:24.852 --> 00:43:27.104
♪ There's no place we can't go ♪

752
00:43:27.187 --> 00:43:29.523
That Clark Bellson
sure does love to drop things.

753
00:43:29.607 --> 00:43:31.692
This one
doesn't involve losing to Castlewood.

754
00:43:31.775 --> 00:43:33.068
so I can forgive him.

755
00:43:33.152 --> 00:43:34.612
What is the matter with you two?

756
00:43:34.695 --> 00:43:38.699
Clark Bellson just agreed
to sell us the Bellwether. At our price!

757
00:43:38.782 --> 00:43:41.285
We should be dancing
and hollering for joy.

758
00:43:41.368 --> 00:43:44.038
There's no "just kidding"
at the end of that. is there?

759
00:43:44.121 --> 00:43:45.331
Helen?

760
00:43:45.873 --> 00:43:46.749
There is not.

761
00:43:46.832 --> 00:43:48.250
♪ Here we go ♪

